# PR Commands From Local Main

Use this flow when local development always happens on `main`.

1. Ensure local `main` is up to date:
   - `git checkout main`
   - `git pull origin main`

2. Commit local changes:
   - `git add -A`
   - `git commit -m "<message>"`

3. Push local `main` HEAD to a remote branch (without creating a local branch):
   - `BRANCH="feature/$(date +%Y-%m-%d)-short-description"`
   - `git push origin HEAD:refs/heads/$BRANCH`

4. Open a PR to `main`:
   - `gh pr create --base main --head "$BRANCH" --title "<title>" --body "<body>"`
